needs arduino ide (hfp on armhf)

get arduino ide
1. download [arduino ide for udoo](http://www.udoo.org/downloads/#tab4) and move it to {arduino_dir}
2. create symlink to arduino: sudo ln -s {arduino_dir} /usr/share/arduino
3. fix version in /usr/share/arduino/lib/version.txt by replacing ${version} with 1.5.4

get ino
1. sudo apt-get install python-pip
2. sudo pip install jinja2 pySerial
3. git clone https://github.com/justonia/ino.git --branch ide1.5x
4. git apply --ignore-space-change --ignore-whitespace patch
5. sudo make install

if permission denied errors run the scripts as sudo or follow these steps to aquire write permissions
1. sudo chown -RL {user} /sys/class/gpio
2. sudo chown {user} /dev/ttymxc3

if missing python modules to run ino
1. sudo pip install {module_name}

on armhf, if bossac is not working, try this:
1. readelf -a bossac | grep interpreter
      [Requesting program interpreter: /lib/ld-linux.so.3]
2. ls /lib | grep ld-linux
      ld-linux-armhf.so.3
3. sudo ln -s /lib/ld-linux-armhf.so.3 /lib/ld-linux.so.3
